cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with image classification using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses strategies for dealing with noisy data, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of machine learning algorithms for classification falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with geographic knowledge discovery, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
